{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f05a5877-9de7-4d7b-82d8-41ae3a004f62","content":"Here's the plan and architecture for your RAG-based Q&A feature:\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n```\n┌─────────────┐      ┌──────────────────┐      ┌────────────────┐\n│  Docs/*.md  │─────▶│ Ingestion Service │─────▶│ Vector Store   │\n└─────────────┘      │ (chunk + embed)   │      │ (in-memory or  │\n                     └──────────────────┘      │  external DB)  │\n                                                └───────┬────────┘\n                                                        │\n┌─────────────┐      ┌──────────────────┐              │\n│  User Query │─────▶│  Query Endpoint  │──── search ──┘\n└─────────────┘      │  POST /ask       │\n                     └───────┬──────────┘\n                             │ top-K chunks\n                             ▼\n                     ┌──────────────────┐\n                     │   LLM (OpenAI /  │\n                     │   Azure OpenAI)  │──▶ Grounded Answer\n                     └──────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Components\n\n| Layer | Responsibility | Suggested Package |\n|-------|---------------|-------------------|\n| **Chunking** | Split markdown by heading/paragraph, ~500 tokens per chunk | `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` or custom splitter |\n| **Embedding** | Convert chunks → vectors | `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` (OpenAI/Azure OpenAI embeddings) |\n| **Vector Store** | Store & similarity-search embeddings | `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData` + in-memory provider (swap for Qdrant/Azure AI Search later) |\n| **Query orchestration** | Embed query → retrieve top-K → build prompt → call LLM | Custom service using `IChatClient` |\n| **LLM generation** | Answer grounded on retrieved context | Azure OpenAI / OpenAI via `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` |\n\n---\n\n## Endpoints\n\n| Method | Route | Purpose |\n|--------|-------|---------|\n| `POST` | `/ingest` | Reads `Docs/` folder, chunks, embeds, and stores vectors |\n| `POST` | `/ask` | Accepts `{ \"question\": \"...\" }`, returns `{ \"answer\": \"...\", \"sources\": [...] }` |\n\n---\n\n## Ingestion Pipeline (POST /ingest)\n\n1. Enumerate `Docs/*.md`\n2. For each file, split into chunks (by markdown headings, then by token limit ~500)\n3. Generate embeddings for each chunk\n4. Store `{ id, text, embedding, source_file, heading }` in the vector store\n\n---\n\n## Query Pipeline (POST /ask)\n\n1. Embed the user question\n2. Similarity search → top 3–5 chunks\n3. Build a system prompt: _\"Answer using ONLY the provided context. Cite sources.\"_\n4. Send `[system + context + user question]` to LLM\n5. Return answer + source metadata\n\n---\n\n## NuGet Packages Needed\n\n- `Microsoft.Extensions.AI.OpenAI` — chat + embeddings\n- `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData.Abstractions` — vector store abstraction\n- `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData.InMemory` — zero-infrastructure dev store\n\n---\n\n## Considerations\n\n- **Chunking strategy**: Heading-aware splitting preserves context better than blind token windows.\n- **Startup ingestion**: Optionally auto-ingest on app start via `IHostedService` so `/ingest` is only needed for refresh.\n- **Scalability**: The in-memory store works for a small doc set; swap the provider for a persistent store (Qdrant, Azure AI Search) when the corpus grows.\n- **Config**: API keys and model names go in `appsettings.json` / env vars.\n\n---\n\nWant me to implement this?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a4ad4657-78b2-4639-a5e9-5af8359d2899","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a clear picture of the project. It's a minimal .NET 10 Web API with two markdown documentation files. The user wants a RAG (Retrieval Augmented Generation) Q&A feature. Let me create a comprehensive plan.","outputTokens":1031,"requestId":"5C38:22A1A7:5DA232:6CCA4D:69FAA4D6"},"id":"bd845a29-5e65-4904-ac77-51133e969ff2","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:18:20.419Z","parentId":"7a227b7d-00f4-40ca-8e30-a1a5ecc8af64"}
